OL,3,CDo you have what it takes to become an
OL,4,Con-call firefighter?
OL,6,FOnce I was on the other side, I
OL,7,Fthought my work was done, but no. I
OL,8,Fwas blindfolded and had to do the same
OL,9,Fcourse backwards.
OL,11,FTo my surprise, this part was less
OL,12,Fscary and claustrophobic than the
OL,13,Ffirst time around. I think because I
OL,14,Fhad to concentrate so much, I wasn't
OL,15,Fpaying attention to the small spaces
OL,16,Fwe were in.
OL,18,FBy the end of my time there, I was
OL,19,Faching, sore, and tired, but
OL,20,Fcompletely buzzing from the adrenaline
OL,21,Frush and endorphins.
